{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Nexivo — API & Signaling",
    "description": "# Nexivo\n\nREST API (default **:4001**) + **Socket.IO** signaling server (default **:4002**). Same **JWT** for `Authorization: Bearer` and Socket.IO handshake auth.\n\n---\n\n## Collection variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| `baseUrl` | `http://localhost:4001` | REST API |\n| `signalingUrl` | `http://127.0.0.1:4002` | Signaling HTTP health + Socket.IO base URL |\n| `token` | *(empty)* | Filled by **Login** / **Register** tests |\n| `meetingCode` | *(empty)* | Filled by **Create meeting** test |\n\n---\n\n## Socket.IO in Postman\n\nPostman **v10+** supports **Socket.IO** as a request type (not plain WebSocket).\n\n1. **Create** → **Socket.IO** request.\n2. **Server URL**: use `{{signalingUrl}}` (e.g. `http://127.0.0.1:4002`) — use **http/https**, not `ws://`.\n3. **Handshake → Auth** (JSON), matching the server:\n   ```json\n   { \"token\": \"{{token}}\" }\n   ```\n   Run **Login** or **Register** first so `{{token}}` is set.\n4. **Connect**, then **emit**:\n   - `meeting:join` — payload: a **JSON string** (the meeting code), e.g. `\"abc123xyz\"` or use the raw string per your Postman version.\n   - `meeting:leave` — no payload.\n   - `webrtc:offer` / `webrtc:answer` / `webrtc:ice` — object must include `\"to\": \"<target socket id>\"` (plus SDP/ICE fields as your app sends).\n5. **Listen** for: `meeting:peer-joined`, `meeting:peer-left`, `webrtc:offer`, `webrtc:answer`, `webrtc:ice`.\n\n**Note:** Engine.IO level is **v4** (`EIO=4`). If you use raw WebSocket instead of Socket.IO mode, you must speak the Engine.IO/Socket.IO protocol; prefer the built-in **Socket.IO** request type.\n\n---\n\n## TLS / LAN\n\nIf the API uses HTTPS (`HTTPS_KEY_PATH` / `HTTPS_CERT_PATH`), set `baseUrl` to `https://...` accordingly. Match **http vs https** between the page and signaling (see server logs).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:4001" },
    { "key": "signalingUrl", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:4002" },
    {
      "key": "signalingWsUrl",
      "value": "ws://127.0.0.1:4002/socket.io/?EIO=4&transport=websocket"
    },
    { "key": "token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "meetingCode", "value": "" },
    { "key": "peerSocketId", "value": "" }
  ],
